  "description": "There are three ways to start work on tasks: `ao execute plan/run`, `ao workflow run` (async/daemon), and `ao workflow execute` (sync/no daemon). Users can't tell which to use. Consolidate: keep `workflow run` with a `--sync` flag instead of separate `execute` command, or clearly differentiate naming. `ao execute` is too vague as a top-level command name.",
